    <section><title>DocBook5 Menu Actions</title>In addition, the following default actions are
      available in the <uicontrol>DocBook5</uicontrol> menu when editing in
        <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol> mode:<dl>
          <dlentry id="paste-special-dlentry-5">
            <dt><uicontrol><image href="../img/PasteSpecialDITA16.png" id="image_cf2_csh_ps"/>Paste
              special</uicontrol> submenu</dt>
            <dd>This submenu includes the following special paste actions that are specific to the
            DocBook 5 framework:<dl>
              <dlentry>
                <dt><uicontrol>Paste As XInclude</uicontrol></dt>
                <dd>Allows you to create an <codeph>xi:include</codeph> element that references a
                  DocBook element copied from <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol> mode. The operation
                  fails if the copied element does not have a declared ID. </dd>
              </dlentry>
              <dlentry>
                <dt><uicontrol>Paste as link</uicontrol></dt>
                <dd>Allows you to create a <codeph>link</codeph> element that references a DocBook
                  element copied from <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol> mode. The operation fails if the
                  copied element does not have a declared ID.</dd>
              </dlentry>
              <dlentry>
                <dt><uicontrol>Paste as xref</uicontrol></dt>
                <dd>Allows you to create an <codeph>xref</codeph> element that references a DocBook
                  element copied from <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol> mode. The operation fails if the
                  copied element does not have a declared ID.</dd>
              </dlentry>
            </dl></dd>
          </dlentry>
